		"body": "\r\nFixes #14747\r\n### **Problem**\r\nOn Android, creating a new to-do while edit mode is active could focus the title field without opening the keyboard. If the title field was tapped and typing started, the keyboard could then dismiss unexpectedly.\r\n\r\n\r\n### **Solution**\r\nThis change updates note focus behavior on mobile so it matches expected behavior in both scenarios.\r\nFor newly created provisional to-dos, focus handling now tolerates Android timing around navigation so the keyboard appears reliably when title autofocus is expected.\r\nFor existing notes, title re-focus is prevented in view mode, so opening an existing note does not auto-focus a field or open the keyboard.\r\nThe title input behavior was also adjusted to avoid focus loss during title layout changes, which prevents the keyboard from being dismissed while typing.\r\n### **Test Plan**\r\nAutomated\r\n\r\nRan targeted note screen tests and confirmed they pass.\r\n### **Manual (Android)**\r\n\r\nOpen an existing note.\r\nExpected: no focused field, no keyboard shown.\r\nWhile edit mode is active, create a new to-do.\r\nExpected: title is focused and keyboard appears.\r\nStart typing in title.\r\nExpected: keyboard remains visible.\r\n### ** Video**\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/75330ff7-9090-43e6-bc72-4bdbb441b7e9\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
