			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nRestricts autofocus to edit mode in the Note component and adds an Android-specific focus-retry loop with timing/grace rules. Adds tests that mock focusHandler, provide a provisional-note helper, and verify autofocus for new notes and absence of autofocus for existing notes.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Tests** <br> `packages/app-mobile/components/screens/Note/Note.test.tsx`|Adds `focusHandler` mock and exposes focus for assertions; introduces `openProvisionalNote` test helper; resets mocks in beforeEach; adds autofocus tests for provisional to-dos and non-autofocus behaviour for existing notes; minor type hints and test utility types.|\n|**Focus & Retry Logic** <br> `packages/app-mobile/components/screens/Note/Note.tsx`|Restricts title autofocus to edit mode; implements Android-specific `scheduleFocusUpdate` retry loop with `wasFocused`/`didFocus` tracking, minimum retry duration (350ms), and termination/grace rules; removes TextInput key-based render optimisation.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\nmermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n  participant Note as Note component\n  participant Focus as focusHandler\n  participant System as Android Keyboard/System\n  Note->>Focus: scheduleFocusUpdate(field)\n  Note->>Note: start retry loop (wasFocused=false, didFocus=false, grace timer)\n  Note->>Focus: attempt focus(field)\n  Focus-->>Note: focus result (success/failure)\n  alt focus succeeded\n    Note->>Note: set didFocus=true, wasFocused=true if applicable\n    Note->>System: request keyboard show\n  else focus failed or before minDuration\n    Note->>Note: continue retries until minDuration elapsed or editor hidden or field cleared\n  end\n\n## Possibly related PRs\n\n- laurent22/joplin#14533: Modifies Note focus/keyboard behaviour and touches title/key handling; closely related to the autofocus changes here.\n\n## Suggested reviewers\n\n- laurent22\n- Kaushalendra-Marcus\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 6</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (6 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|              Title check              | ✅ Passed | The title clearly and specifically describes the main fix: addressing Android keyboard focus issues when creating new to-dos on mobile.                                                                                                           |\n|          Linked Issues check          | ✅ Passed | The changeset addresses all coding requirements from issue `#14747`: reliable keyboard focus for new provisional to-dos [`#14747`], prevented auto-focus in view mode [`#14747`], and prevented keyboard dismissal during typing [`#14747`].              |\n|       Out of Scope Changes check      | ✅ Passed | All changes are directly scoped to the linked issue: focus retry logic for Android navigation timing, mode-aware focus triggering, test additions for autofocus verification, and TextInput optimisations.                                        |\n|           Docstring Coverage          | ✅ Passed | No functions found in the changed files to evaluate docstring coverage. Skipping docstring coverage check.                                   